Description: Fragment of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Oval handle, curving. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-buff; cream slip.
Curator's comments: Probably drawn by Petrie (Petrie diary, 1884-1885 (EES Archive XVII 47), p.136, 1. Name Mikythos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0389.32.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0545)
